title: Agencies Say They Need Access to Americans' Emails Without a Warrant
text:
21 Agencies Say They Need Access to Americans' Emails Without a Warrant 
Government Executive: A bi­par­tis­an bid to re­form an elec­tron­ic-pri­vacy law has the sup­port of the tech com­munity and the White House, but fed­er­al law en­force­ment of­fi­cials tell Con­gress the changes would hamper civil pro­sec­u­tion.
